When the mellow moon begins to beam,
Every night I dream a little dream;
And of course Prince Charming is the theme:
The he
For me.
Although I realize as well as you
It is seldom that a dream comes true,
To me it's clear
That he'll appear.

Some day he'll come along,
The man I love;
And he'll be big and strong,
The man I love;
And when he comes my way,
I'll do my best to make him stay.

Skyline seems to disappear
When your lonely in New York
Sidewalks don't lead anywhere
When your lonely in New York

Rush hour traffic not a soul around
The echo of your heart beat makes the only sound
Broadway is a dead end street
When your lonely in New York

Rockefeller Center doesn't rock
...

I feel pretty
Oh so pretty
I feel pretty and witty and bright
And I pity any girl who isn't me tonight.

I feel charming
Oh so charming
It's alarming how charming I feel
And so pretty that I hardly can believe I'm real.

See the pretty girl in that mirror there
Who can that attractive girl be?
Such a pretty face
Such a pretty dress
Such a pretty smile
Such a pretty me!

I feel stunning
And entrancing
Feel like running and dancing for joy
For I'm loved by a pretty wonderful boy!

Have you met my good friend Maria
...

When my hugs her he whispers to me, I see life in pink. He tells me words of love, Words of every day And it makes me something. He entered my heart A part of happiness ...
While tearing off a game of golf, 
I may make a play for the caddy, 
But if I do, I don't follow through
Cause my heart belongs to daddy.

If I invite a boy some night
To dine on my fine finnan haddie, 
I just adore his asking for more, cause
My heart belongs to daddy.

Yes, my heart belongs to daddy, 
And I simply couldn't be bad.
Yes my heart belongs to daddy.
